[Student "S"]
{North is to play 3NT. East leads the \HK.

Winners:   \S=3  \H=1  \D=0  \C=4  Total = 8

Unless there is a miracle in the \Ds, (or a defensive error), you can't get a trick in that suit. But you have a chance for a second \H trick.

It's the Bath Coup again, just dressed up a little differently. 

Let East hold the first trick, playing the \H7 from your hand to conceal the \H4 in the hope that East will continue the suit. If he does you have your ninth trick - if he doesn't, good luck.

Compare this Bath Coup to the one in Deal 10.}
[Play "W"]HK

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "E:T953.AK4.AQ7.K63 KJ872.T75.T94.A5 A6.632.K53.QJT94 Q4.QJ98.J862.872"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "3NT"]
